I got to update my last year’s header illustration for the @nytimes Book Review for the international literature section Globetrotting.
What I did was increasing fidelity and add more books and some additional objects. Color got a bit of an update, too.
If you swipe you can see the 2019 version and the very first version that was rejected for obvious reasons. I’ve always known that my color decisions come from a very subconscious place. Even though I have set of color palettes I work with, I usually tweak them in the process until the piece ‘feels right’. Guess it’s easy to tell when I wasn’t feeling too upbeat. (The muddy version and the 2019 version have basically been made at the same time, but I had to put in a lot of effort and convincing myself to make the 2019 version this ‘vibrant’) .
.

READS

October reads. 
Exhalation: Had exactly two good and one very good story in it. 
The Sixth Extinction: Non fiction horror about what has already happened and a taste of what’s still to come. Please read. 
November reads. 
A Little History About Philosophy: Quick, nice, light. Nigel also has a podcast called Philosophy Bites which I’ve been listening to for many years. He’s good with words. 
Pachinko: Genius in most ways. The language was the only letdown. 
Trick Mirror: Very very well written report on societal issues of the years 2016-2019 ¯\_(ツ)_/¯ .
.
.
.
.
